  "body": "**Is this a bug report or feature request?**\r\n* Feature Request\r\n\r\n**What should the feature do:**\r\n\r\nWhen a metadata PVC is used for OSD on PVC, allow the crushDeviceClassFlag to be set to something distinct like 'hybrid' or 'mixed'\r\n\r\n**What is use case behind this feature:**\r\n\r\nA cluster might have some hosts with\r\n\r\n1. TLC flash devices (metadata and data) - eg. for block and file pools, object index/multisite pools\r\n2. Optane (metadata) and QLC flash devices (data)- eg. for object data pools\r\n\r\nIn these circumstances, both would be \"ssd\" device class because rotational is set to `0` for the data device. Clearly the performance is different, despite neither being rotational.\r\n\r\n\r\n",
